   11123       11729 : static void calculate_implicit_abi_tags(a_source_correspondence *scp,
   11124             :                                         an_il_entry_kind        kind)
   11125             : /*
   11126             : Determine the implicit abi_tags that apply to the given IL entity (a variable
   11127             : or routine -- as specified by "kind"), if any, and create a new abi_tag
   11128             : attribute with their values.
   11129             : 
   11130             : The method for determining how to compute implicit abi_tags is not well
   11131             : documented, consisting of a single sentence: "When a type involving an ABI tag
   11132             : is used as the type of a variable or return type of a function where that tag
   11133             : is not already present in the signature of the function, the tag is
   11134             : automatically applied to the variable or function."
   11135             : 
   11136             : As implemented here, this involves three steps:
   11137             : 
   11138             :   1. Marking every entity that contributes to the "mangled signature" of
   11139             :      the entity.
   11140             :   2. Visiting all components of the type (return type for routines and variable
   11141             :      type for variables) and adding implicit abi_tags for any component that
   11142             :      is not marked in step 1 and has an explicit abi_tag.
   11143             :   3. Re-visiting the entities in step 1 to reset the marks.
   11144             : */
   11145             : {
   11146             : #if ABI_COMPATIBILITY_VERSION >= 411
